{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how verification commands for session_log AC items will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f01d236e10a618469","f3ef31726167ce83a","f46aff46e860a86d1","f4b111f707439f98b","f0106435c61800978"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"verification commands for session_log AC items"},{"coaching":"Pin down ticket-model proving command pattern coverage with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f26ba73e691a3e319"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"ticket-model proving command pattern coverage"},{"coaching":"Plan how section-scoped verification for concurrency I4a will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fa6dd81c93117e6c6"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"section-scoped verification for concurrency I4a"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] semantic completeness attestation mechanism will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f5a7a22d931910bba"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"semantic completeness attestation mechanism"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for which acceptance criteria set governs execution — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f3f0f9a89d9d4b55d","f1005b1b124c667b6"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"which acceptance criteria set governs execution"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for copy-faithfully vs. no-restate contradiction.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f220d923790a39fb3"],